It seems like Twitter Cards has moved away from detecting `<meta property="twitter:image" ...>`, because I noticed that the images I provided to my blog posts stopped showing up in my Twitter Cards. [This StackOverflow answer](https://stackoverflow.com/a/71063178/505996) caused me to look into the issue and sure enough, [the Twitter documentation](https://developer.twitter.com/en/docs/twitter-for-websites/cards/overview/summary) now uses `meta name` instead of `meta property`.

When I tried to verify this using the following dirty hack...

```
    {% capture seoWithProperTwitterMetaTags %}
    {% seo %}
    {% endcapture %}

    <!-- because of https://stackoverflow.com/a/71063178/505996 -->
    {{ seoWithProperTwitterMetaTags | replace: 'property="twitter:image"', 'name="twitter:image"' }}
```

...it turned out this was actually the issue, because the images started showing up on my Twitter Cards again.

So I want to suggest to change `<meta property="twitter:image" ...>` to `<meta name="twitter:image" ...>`.

